						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the well called <hi rend="italic">gāḍibhāvi,</hi> to the north of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1702 Śārvari, Jyēshṭha śu. 5, A.H. 1192,</hi> corresponding to 1780 A.D., August 5, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It registers a grant of land situated in the <hi rend="italic">Jāgīr</hi> of Hazarat Ummar Sha made by Mirja Mahamad Bēku, to Pagiḍēla Kṛishnamma for filling with water the trough constructed by the former.</p>						

						</summary>
